  //////////////////////////
 // rsmvc.googlecode.com //
//////////////////////////

REQUIREMENTS:
  - PHP >= 5.3.0 (PDO and object model)
  - Apache's mod_rewrite

INSTALLING
  - Enable Apache's mod_rewrite.
  - Make /system/tmp/ and subfolders writable (chmod).
  - Read and edit /app/configs/config.php.

CONTROLLER
  /app/controllers/examplename.php (lowercase filename)
  class ExampleName extends Controller

  $this->view->save( $key [, $value = NULL ] )
  Save a variable (or set of variables when $key is an associative array).

  $this->view->display( $fileName [, $caching = FALSE [, $cacheId = NULL ]] )
  Prints the view.

  $this->view->fetch( $fileName [, $caching = FALSE [, $cacheId = NULL ]] )
  Returns the view.

  $this->view->isCached( $fileName [, $cacheId = NULL ] )
  Checks if the view is cached.

  $this->view->clearCache([ $fileName = NULL [, $cacheId = NULL ]] )
  Deletes the given view's cache or entire cache directory.

MODEL
  /app/models/*.php
  class * extends Model

  $this->db-> ( query( $sql ) | exec( $sql ) | quote( $string ) | lastInsertId( void ) )
  PDO instance. Enable this by uncommenting the $config['db'] lines in /app/configs/config.php.

VIEW
  /app/views/*.php

  $config
  Returns the config (array).

  NOTE: The following 3 variables only work with the View::display() method.
  #timer# is replaced by the page's total load time in seconds.
  #queries# is replaced by the amount of database queries called.
  #queryTimer# is replaced by the query load time in seconds.

GLOBAL HELPERS
  RSMVC::getConfig([ $key = NULL ])
  Returns the config or part of the config when $key is set.

  RSMVC::setConfig( $key [, $value = NULL ] )
  If $key is an array, it will array_merge itself with the existing config. Else if $value is NULL, it unsets the $key row.

  RSMVC::redirect( $location [, $statusCode = 302 ] )
  Creates a local redirect. (Format: "link/to/path/")

  RSMVC::errorPage( $errorCode [, $message = NULL ] )
  Prints an error page. If $message is not set, /app/views/errorPage.php will print one based on the $errorCode.